'''Peter Lorange''' (born 17 April 1943) is a Norwegian economist. He was the owner, President, and CEO of the Lorange Institute of Business Zürich,<ref>[http://www.lorange.org/en/about-us.aspx Lorange.Org] Lorange Institute of Business Website (Team), Retrieved Feb 16, 2014</ref>{{Not in citation|date=April 2018}} formerly known as GSBA Zurich, which he bought in July 2009.<ref>[http://www.mba-channel.com/channel/article/gsba-imd-peter-lorange/ MBA Channel: Former IMD president buys GSBA]</ref>{{Not in citation|date=April 2018}}
Peter Lorange has previously been President of the [[International Institute for Management Development]] (IMD) and President of the [[BI Norwegian Business School]]. He has taught at the [[Wharton School]], [[University of Pennsylvania]] and at the [[MIT Sloan School of Management]].{{cn|date=April 2018}}
He recently founded the Lorange Network,<ref>[http://www.lorangenetwork.com Lorange Network]</ref> a learning and sharing platform for family office principals and family business owners.
Lorange received his undergraduate education from the [[Norwegian School of Economics]], was awarded an MA degree in operations management from [[Yale University]], and his [[Doctor of Business Administration]] degree from [[Harvard University]].{{cn|date=April 2018}}
He is both a business academic and a successful entrepreneur with his own shipping company S. Ugelstad.{{cn|date=April 2018}}
== Selected publications == * Lorange, Peter, and [[Johan Roos]]. ''Strategic alliances: Formation, implementation, and evolution.'' (1993).
