{{Infobox journal | title = Trusts & Trustees | cover = | discipline = [[Trust law]] | abbreviation = Trusts Trustees | editor = Toby Graham, [[Anthony Molloy (lawyer)|Tony Molloy]] | publisher = [[Oxford University Press]] | country = | history = 1994-present | frequency = 10/year | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://tandt.oxfordjournals.org/ | link1 = http://tandt.oxfordjournals.org/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://tandt.oxfordjournals.org/archive | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 1363-1780 | eISSN = 1752-2110 | OCLC = 475595973 | LCCN = 2007211006 }} '''''Trusts & Trustees''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[law journal]] published ten times per year by [[Oxford University Press]]. The journal covers [[trust law]] and practice, including case notes on topical cases and updates on trends and developments from around the world. The [[editors-in-chief]] are Toby Graham (Farrer & Co., United Kingdom) and David Russell QC (barrister, Outer Temple Chambers Dubai and London, and Chairman of the STEP International Client Special Interest Group).
